President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Michael T. Harvey as Assistant Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID) for the Middle East Bureau. Harvey, a career USAID Foreign Service officer, is currently a faculty member at the National War College and previously led USAID's Defeat ISIS Task Force. Trump also intends to nominate Alan Ray Shaffer as Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition and Sustainment. Shaffer previously served as Director of NATO Science and Technology and Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering. Lastly, Trump intends to appoint Gary Washington as a Member of the Commodity Credit Corporation, Board of Directors.